comments: Collins (ATL) firms up in his screening position in Exum's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact.

Nance Jr. (CLE) has his left hand extended forward when marginal contact occurs with Young's (ATL) right arm. The contact occurs before the start of Young's upward shooting motion, and Nance Jr. legally contests his jump shot attempt.
Drummond (CLE) establishes himself in a screening position in Bogdanovic's (ATL) path and does not deliver the contact.
Drummond (CLE) dislodges Capela (ATL) from his position during the rebound.
Bogdanovic (ATL) maintains a rested hand on Exum's (CLE) backside and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Hunter (ATL) cleanly blocks Drummond's (CLE) shot attempt near the rim.
Drummond (CLE) swings down and makes contact across Collins' (ATL) left forearm that affects his ability to control the loose ball.
Collins (ATL) makes incidental contact with Drummond's (CLE) lower half as the ball is loose on the floor.

Before the out of bounds, Collins (ATL) gathers the rebound with two hands, which resets the shot clock to 24. As noted, Drummond (CLE) knocks the ball loose and the ball ultimately goes out of bounds off of him, with 22 left on the shot clock. ATL has a total of eight seconds from the time Collins initially possesses the ball to advance the ball, even if the ball is knocked out of bounds by CLE. When the shot clock reaches 15, ATL has been in continuous possession of the ball in its backcourt for eight seconds (including the time before the out of bounds) and an 8-second violation is called.
Bogdanovic (ATL) and Exum (CLE) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Drummond (CLE) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Sexton (CLE) and Hunter (ATL) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Collins (ATL) is jumping slightly toward Drummond (CLE) when marginal body contact occurs as Drummond is passing the ball while airborne.
Collins (ATL) re-establishes slightly in Exum's (CLE) path after initial contact takes place during the screen, and the contact is marginal.
Exum (CLE) rests his hand on Young's (ATL) side and marginal contact occurs as Young drives into the lane.
Sexton (CLE) and Reddish (ATL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Exum (CLE) brushes Young's (ATL) backside as he receives the pass and marginal body contact occurs.
Exum (CLE) legally contests Collins' (ATL) dunk attempt.
Young (ATL) commits the take foul on Drummond (CLE).
Hunter (ATL) commits the take foul on Garland (CLE).
Collins (ATL) makes incidental contact with Drummond's (CLE) backside as they each attempt to fight for the rebound.
Reddish (ATL) commits the take foul on Sexton (CLE).
Young (ATL) commits the take foul on Sexton (CLE).
